[49m[38;5;10m+    212[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    213[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## General Architecture Pattern
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    214[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    215[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A healthcare care-coordination assistant decomposes into ten logical stages: enrollment and consent, longitudinal-journey-store initialization, channel entry with disclosure, input safety screening with continuous emergency screening, identity-and-context loading with multi-source aggregation, conversation handling with care-plan-grounded responses, output safety screening with scope and citation verification, action execution with referral-tracking and scheduling, navigator and care-team handoff with operational integration, and audit logging with coordination-specific retention discipline. The cross-cutting concerns from recipes 11.1 through 11.8 carry forward; this recipe adds five new ones (multi-source integration with consent-aware retrieval, journey-care-plan governance with care-coordination-leadership ownership, referral-and-appointment lifecycle tracking with stuck-state detection, multi-stakeholder consent posture with caregiver-access granularity, and operational integration with the institution's care-coordination workforce).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    216[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    217[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    218[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── ENROLLMENT + CONSENT ──────────────────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    219[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    220[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Patient enrolls via care-team referral, payer's        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    221[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    care-navigation program, or patient self-enrollment    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    222[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    where the institution offers it]                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    223[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Documented consent specific to coordination          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    224[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      support with care-coordination-leadership and        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    225[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      legal-counsel-reviewed language                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    226[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Journey type designation (oncology, post-cardiac,    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    227[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      post-stroke, complex pregnancy, organ transplant,    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    228[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      pediatric special-needs, multi-comorbidity           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    229[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      geriatric, behavioral-health-plus-medical, others)   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    230[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Caregiver designation with per-caregiver access      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    231[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      scope (full access, appointment-only,                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    232[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      records-only, custom)                                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    233[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Engagement preferences (channel, cadence, quiet      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    234[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      hours, opt-out granularity)                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    235[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Consent for cross-institution information retrieval  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    236[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      (HIE participation, patient-mediated data flow)      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    237[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - State-specific consent variations enforced where     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    238[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      records have enhanced privacy protections beyond     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    239[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      HIPAA baseline (mental health, substance use,        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    240[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      adolescent care, others)                             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    241[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    242[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    243[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: signed consent record; enrollment              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    244[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    confirmation; initialization of journey store]         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    245[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    246[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    247[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    248[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── LONGITUDINAL JOURNEY STORE INIT ──────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    249[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    250[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Per-patient journey store]                             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    251[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active care journeys (one or many concurrent)        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    252[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Journey-specific care plans (structured, signed)     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    253[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Journey milestones with target dates and statuses    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    254[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active providers (PCP, specialists, navigator,       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    255[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      pharmacist, others)                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    256[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active referrals with lifecycle states               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    257[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Scheduled appointments with confirmations            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    258[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Designated caregivers with access scopes             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    259[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Stated patient preferences                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    260[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Conversation history (initially empty)               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    261[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Records-availability ledger                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    262[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Engagement-fatigue indicator                         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    263[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    264[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Storage architecture]                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    265[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Structured data: DynamoDB tables                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    266[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Conversation transcript: S3 with vector retrieval    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    267[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Recent-context summary: cached, refreshed per        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    268[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      conversation                                         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    269[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Sensitive disclosures: separately governed           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    270[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    271[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    272[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: journey store ready for coordination           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    273[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    conversations]                                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    274[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    275[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    276[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    277[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── CHANNEL ENTRY WITH DISCLOSURE ─────────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    278[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    279[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Patient-initiated entry]                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    280[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - In-app chat (most common)                            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    281[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - SMS (where supported, with appropriate consent)      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    282[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Web chat                                             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    283[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Voice channel (where supported)                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    284[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Email (where supported, with reduced PHI scope)      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    285[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    286[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Caregiver-initiated entry, consent-gated]              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    287[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Designated caregiver with their own auth context     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    288[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Conversation scope limited to consent grant          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    289[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    290[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Assistant-initiated entry]                             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    291[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Milestone-driven (pre-appointment, post-discharge,   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    292[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      pre-procedure, post-consult)                         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    293[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Stuck-state-driven (referral pending too long,       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    294[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      records not received, prior auth delayed)            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    295[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Care-team-requested (navigator pushes a check-in     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    296[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      task to the assistant)                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    297[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Engagement is conservative; respects fatigue and     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    298[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      quiet hours                                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    299[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    300[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Disclosure refresh per session or per defined          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    301[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    cadence]                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    302[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - "I'm a chat tool, not a person"                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    303[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - "I help with logistics and coordination; I don't     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    304[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      replace your clinical team"                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    305[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - "If you have an emergency, call 911; if you have     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    306[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      a clinical question, the help button gets you to     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    307[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      a person on your care team"                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    308[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    309[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
