[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    493[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      with confirmation flow back to the patient           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    494[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - reschedule_appointment: same with cancellation       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    495[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - record_transfer_request: writes to records-          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    496[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      management system or HIE portal                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    497[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - prior_auth_status_check: reads from prior-auth       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    498[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      system                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    499[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - referral_status_track: updates referral lifecycle    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    500[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      state in the institution's referral system           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    501[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - caregiver_update_send: composes and sends update     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    502[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      to designated caregiver per consent                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    503[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    504[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Idempotency and confirmation]                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    505[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Each action carries an idempotency key               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    506[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Patient confirms scheduling, rescheduling, and       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    507[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      record-transfer-request actions before they execute  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    508[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Failed actions surface to the patient with retry     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    509[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      options or escalation                                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    510[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    511[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    512[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: action results posted to action-event log]     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    513[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    514[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    515[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    516[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── NAVIGATOR + CARE-TEAM HANDOFF ─────────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    517[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    518[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Handoff triggers]                                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    519[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Stuck-state escalation (referral pending too long,   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    520[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      records not received, prior auth delayed)            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    521[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Patient explicitly requests human                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    522[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Out-of-scope clinical question                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    523[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Sensitive disclosure (IPV, abuse, neglect, severe    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    524[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      side effects)                                        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    525[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Acute symptom routing (joint with triage)            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    526[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Mental-health concern (routes to mental-health       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    527[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      support; navigator notified per policy)              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    528[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Bot confidence below threshold                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    529[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Patient pattern indicates worsening trajectory       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    530[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Care-team-requested escalation                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    531[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    532[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Handoff targets]                                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    533[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active emergency: 911 routing                        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    534[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Acute medical concern: triage workflow               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    535[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Mental-health crisis: mental-health support pathway  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    536[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Stuck operational state: navigator workforce         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    537[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Sensitive disclosure: navigator and (where           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    538[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      mandatory-reporter routing applies) clinical         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    539[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      mandatory-reporter                                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    540[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Out-of-scope clinical question: care-team alert      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    541[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      to PCP or specialty team                             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    542[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Caregiver-coordination concern: navigator            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    543[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    544[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Warm-handoff payload]                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    545[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Recent conversation transcript                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    546[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active journey context                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    547[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Recent referral and appointment statuses             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    548[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Trigger reason                                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    549[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Patient's preferred contact method                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    550[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Caregiver context (where applicable)                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    551[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Bot's structured summary                             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    552[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    553[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Bridge-and-stay pattern]                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    554[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Bot does not just hand the patient a phone number    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    555[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Bot bridges to the navigator workforce queue         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    556[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Bot stays present until handoff is acknowledged      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    557[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Patient does not start over                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    558[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    559[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    560[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: handoff event with structured payload to       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    561[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    appropriate target, conversation continuity preserved] │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    562[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    563[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    564[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    565[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── AUDIT, LOG, AND OUTCOME PIPELINE ──────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    566[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    567[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Durable conversation record]                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    568[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - User and caregiver utterances                        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    569[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Tool calls with arguments and results                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    570[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Generated assistant responses                        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    571[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Action executions (scheduling, transfers)            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    572[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active model and prompt versions                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    573[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active care-plan-content versions                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    574[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Final disposition                                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    575[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    576[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Coordination-specific retention discipline]            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    577[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Retention sized to longest of HIPAA's six-year       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    578[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      minimum, state-specific record retention rules,      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    579[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      institutional policy, and any litigation-hold        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    580[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      obligations                                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    581[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Mental-health and substance-use related              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    582[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      disclosures (where applicable) handled with          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    583[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      enhanced privacy posture                             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    584[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    585[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Outcome correlation as multi-quarter to multi-year     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    586[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    commitment]                                            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    587[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Care-journey-completion rate                         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    588[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Time-to-next-step-after-trigger                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    589[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Referral-loop-closure rate                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    590[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Records-availability-at-point-of-care                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    591[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Patient-reported coordination experience             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    592[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Caregiver-reported coordination experience           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    593[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Hospitalization rate, ED visit rate                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    594[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Per-cohort outcome stratification                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    595[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    596[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Operational telemetry]                                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    597[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Engagement rate by patient cohort                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    598[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Attrition rate by patient cohort                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    599[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Stuck-state-detection rate                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    600[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Stuck-state-resolution time                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    601[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Citation-coverage rate                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    602[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Escalation rate by trigger type                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    603[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Per-cohort metric slices (language, journey type,    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    604[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      age, sex, channel, social-determinant flags)         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    605[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    606[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Sampled clinical and operational quality review]       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    607[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Random sample plus targeted sample of escalations,   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    608[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      stuck-state cases, and low-confidence interactions   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    609[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Reviewers tag failure modes (out-of-scope, scope-    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    610[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      violation, citation-gap, stale-data, stuck-state-    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    611[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      missed, tone-failure, action-error, integration-    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    612[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      failure)                                             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    613[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Care-plan-content revisions driven by review         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    614[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      findings with care-coordination-leadership signoff   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    615[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    616[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    617[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: audit trail, telemetry, learning signals,      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    618[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    care-plan-content-revision proposals]                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    619[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    620[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    621[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    622[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    623[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A few cross-cutting design points specific to the care coordination assistant.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    624[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    625[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Multi-source integration as architectural primitive.** The assistant pulls from many systems with consent-aware retrieval and provenance preservation on every fact. The integration breadth determines the assistant's value; the integration discipline determines its trustworthiness.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    626[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    627[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Journey-care-plan governance with care-coordination-leadership ownership.** Each journey type has structured care-plan templates owned by care-coordination leadership, reviewed before adoption, and reviewed annually. Each piece of care-plan content has defined indications and milestones.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    628[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    629[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Referral-and-appointment lifecycle tracking with stuck-state detection.** Lifecycle states drive appropriate engagement; stuck states drive escalation. The detection logic is operational architecture, not LLM judgment.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    630[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    631[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Multi-stakeholder consent posture with caregiver-access granularity.** The assistant interacts with patients and (with consent) designated caregivers, with role-specific scope and tone. Consent is patient-controlled, granular, revocable.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    632[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    633[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Operational integration with the institution's care-coordination workforce.** The assistant escalates to the workforce; the workforce can also push tasks back to the assistant. The integration is workflow-deep.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    634[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    635[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Citation discipline as architectural primitive.** Every fact about the patient's record is grounded in cited retrieved data with provenance preserved.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    636[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    637[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Conservative-bias-default policy.** When data is missing, stale, or ambiguous, the assistant says so rather than inventing facts. When the conversation drifts toward clinical judgment, the assistant routes.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    638[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    639[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Per-cohort monitoring is non-negotiable.** Engagement, attrition, stuck-state-resolution, citation-coverage, escalation, and outcome metrics vary by language, channel, journey type, age, sex, and social-determinant flags.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    640[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    641[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Disaster-recovery topology.** When any source system is unreachable, the assistant degrades gracefully. The minimum behavior is "I'm having trouble connecting to the system right now. I will let your care coordinator know, and they will follow up. If you have an emergency, please call 911." The graceful degradation paths are exercised in tabletop drills.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    642[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    643[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
